The paper deals with the problem of opinion spam detection in online consumer reviews, which is a topic that falls under the broad area of information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to detect and characterize abnormal events in real-time, which could fall under the sub-categories of statistical learning (cs.LG) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of spam detection, which could fall under the sub-category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of temporal data, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
